  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-7-1685710185381-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-7-1685710185381-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-7-1685710185381-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-7-1685710185381-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-7-1685710185381-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>pepper[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon)</p><p>Cut your <strong>avocado[s]</strong> in half lengthways, around the <strong>stone[s]</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>stone[s]</strong> using a spoon, then scoop out the <strong>avocado flesh</strong> and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1685710188781-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1685710188781-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1685710188781-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1685710188781-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1685710188781-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved pepper </strong>(hollow side of the pepper facing up) to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray under the grill for an initial 7-8 min or until the pepper is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
