          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pepper is softening, add the <strong>diced shallot</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) to a bowl with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> mayo</strong> to the bowl and stir it all together – this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot mayo</strong></p>",
